This paper deals with the issue of profile matching across multiple online social networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses privacy concerns, which could be classified under cybersecurity (cs.CR) or data privacy (cs.DB). The evaluation methodology proposed in the paper involves analyzing large datasets, which could be categorized under data management (cs.DB) or statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a set of properties for profile attributes, which could be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY).
